Response to Medication Use in HF Patients

Baker Bioinformatics - 15 November 2021

1 Study Design

Objective

Here we use the UK Biobank to look at response to medication us in participants with Heart Failure (HF).

Schematic of the study design

Schematic of the study design

2 Study Plan

Study Plan

  1. Get HF Individuals (Self Reported and ICD10 codes)

  1. Get Medication Use (Names for Each Class and match with UKB Medication code)

    1. Survival Information (Names for Each Class and match with UKB Medication code)

2.1 HF selection

Schematic of Heart Failure Sample Selection. Heart Failure was defined using the inclusion/exclusion criterion previously published in Shah et al (2020) https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-019-13690-5

4.1 Death Information

4.2 Survival Analysis

KM Survival Curve - Stratified by Medication Use!

Kaplan-Meier survival curves stratified by Medication Frequency, Not Adjusted for any Covariates.

The number at risk" table for medication use is provided below the survival curve.

Medication Frequency means take either no medication (FreqMed=0); 1 medication type (FreqMed=1); 2 or more medication type (FreqMed = 2+).

Survival rates are higher in HF for those who take No Medication or 1 particular type of medication.

Does this people who take multiple medication (2 or more types) are more sicker or have been taking medication way before HF diagnosis????.
